Create my seperate components; 

To create a more comprehensive Ethereum Block Explorer in React, you can add features such as fetching block details, displaying transaction information, and implementing navigation between different blocks. Below is an expanded example with additional components:

Create Components:
Start by creating separate components for different parts of the explorer:

BlockList.js:
A component to display a list of blocks.

BlockDetails.js:
A component to display details of a specific block, including transactions.

Navigation.js:
A component for navigating between different blocks.